This paper investigates the consumption of popular videos on YouTube across different countries, which involves analyzing data and using statistical methods. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CY (Computers and Society), which deals with the social and ethical aspects of computing. 

The paper also examines the influence of cultural values on cross-cultural video consumption, which falls under the scope of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SOC (Social and Cultural Anthropology). 

Furthermore, the paper analyzes the popularity of videos, which is related to cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). 

Overall, the most likely categories are cs.CY, cs.SI, and cs.SOC, followed by cs.MM and cs.HC.
